body:
IMHO neither the client nor the adapter should make any assumptions about the protocol version to use for outgoing requests.

@frent You can use `\Cake\Http\Client::send()` with a custom request object, where you can define things the way you need them. Or you can create a custom adapter that forces a specific protocol version by overriding `\Cake\Http\Client\Adapter\Curl::getProtocolVersion()`.

Maybe there should be an easy way to process the automatically generated request object when using the client's shorthand methods, something like a callback option where one can modify the object before it's being passed to the adapter, idk.

`$http = new Client();
        $response = $http->post($url, [
          'fields' => $fields,
          'key' => $key,
        ]`

It's a real simple Curl Post trough the Client. And it worked until recently with the updates mentioned above. But should the HTTP version be sent along with the CURL request then?
